{"id": "1407028141045583944", "channel_id": "1407028141045583944", "type": 0, "author_id": "149294390924279809", "author_name": "yunayukivrc", "author_bot": false, "content": "I am on story chapter 4, and after the update rolled out, any text that has more than 2 lines of dialogue speeds up to the next line and scrolls down until it reaches the last 2. This sometimes leaves no time to read the first lines, specially when the text is 4 lines long, where it almost instantly disappears from view. Attemping to scroll back up by clicking and dragging does not work, and only forwards to the next text, while the scroll wheel also doesn't do anything to scroll the text back. Only means so far to see the entire text with this is to open the text log on the top right corner, which comes with another problem as it does not let you forward to the next dialogue unless you close it and click on the screen. Is this intentional or a bug? And if it is intentional, is there a way to fix it or any plans for settings regarding this?\nI'd like to suggest the option to drag the text to scroll it up with the mouse, and to be able to forward the dialogue text while in the text log screen.", "timestamp": "2025-08-18T15:47:30.144000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-08-18T15:48:23.044000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "😲", "emoji_id": null, "count": 6}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407028141045583944", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Text auto-scrolling down on PC version after update", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "is_thread_starter": true, "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361168893200044183"]}
